A Berkshire, aka 2-8-4. The type was developed from the Mikado type (2-8-2) The second set of trailing wheels allowing a very large firebox for high-speed passenger operations. The Berkshire was promoted by the United States Railroad Administration (the USA socialized the railroads during WW I) and became common from the 1920's through the '50's.
